 one another (and, indeed, to anything other) insofar as we conceal as well.Key FeaturesDevelops a unique reading of the later work of the philosopher Jacques Derrida, particularly his largely overlooked discussions of the secret in his writings and seminarsCompares Derrida’s work on the secret with other important political thinkers, including Deleuze, Schmitt, Arendt, Bataille and AgambenDraws parallels with the work of German sociologist Georg Simmel, showing Derrida's significance for sociological thoughtConnects Derrida’s work to a series of philosophical debates in the analytic tradition, such as the problems of consciousness, self-deception and other minds  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aSecrecyxPhilosophy. 4aPhilosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311078140340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978147442501840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781474425018423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781474425018/original  a978-3-11-078140-3  Edinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK